# Development server

After making code changes in a session, ensure the Vite development server is
running (`npm run dev`).

- Before starting it, check existing terminals / port `5173` so you do not start
  a second copy if one is already up.
- If it is not running, start it in the background from the repo root and leave
  it running.
- Do this whenever you finish a batch of edits that the user would want to try
  in the browser — no need for the user to ask each time.
- This is separate from iOS deploy (`npm run ios`); web changes still get the
  local dev server.
